parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle surges forward
the fuel pump runs continuously
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the hybrid system can cause the vehicle to decelerate or stall while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle decelerates or stalls while driving
the hybrid system malfunction warning light comes on
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of power can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power while driving
the vehicle stalls or hesitates
and the vehicle may not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning SOS system can cause an ear-splitting screech through the speakers, potentially damaging hearing and creating a distraction while driving.
symptoms: Intermittent
extremely loud
high-pitched screeching sound through the speakers when starting the vehicle
accompanied by flashing red and green lights near the SOS button.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause a loud, intermittent "squeak" type noise when applying the brakes, potentially leading to a loss of braking power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent "squeak" type noise when applying the brakes
which may be accompanied by a brief warning lamp flash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof glass can cause a loud explosion noise, potentially distracting the driver and creating a hazard from falling glass.
symptoms: Loud explosion noise
followed by the shattering of the sunroof glass
which may fall onto the driver and passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning Bluetooth hands-free system can cause an echo of the caller's voice, potentially distracting the driver and creating a safety risk.
symptoms: Echo of the caller's voice when using the Bluetooth hands-free system
which may require the driver to adjust the volume settings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of substandard glass in the windshield can increase the risk of breakage, potentially causing accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Multiple instances of windshield breakage
potentially requiring frequent replacements.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning hybrid system can cause the vehicle to slip into drive without engaging the hybrid system, potentially leading to a loss of braking power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle slips into drive without engaging the hybrid system
allowing the vehicle to roll without brakes or steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning low pressure fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, potentially leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle may stall while driving
potentially due to a malfunctioning low pressure fuel pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning navigation system can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete loss of voice guidance from the navigation system
potentially causing the driver to glance at the display and increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause a loss of power and increase the risk of accidents, particularly in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Engine stalling or sputtering
potentially accompanied by a choppy or uneven movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loud wind noise can be a distraction while driving, potentially increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud wind noise while driving
potentially due to a faulty door or window seal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear humming or buzzing sound can be a distraction while driving, potentially increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent humming or buzzing sound from the rear of the vehicle when turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent High-Pitched Beeping Noise and SOS System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden, loud noise can startle the driver and passengers, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Loud
ear-splitting beeping noise
flashing green and red lights near the SOS button
and intermittent failure of the SOS system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Vehicle Stalling or Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling or loss of power
inability to accelerate
jerking or sputtering
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Drain and Electrical System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic, and can also leave the vehicle stranded.
symptoms: Random battery drain
inability to start the vehicle
and electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration can cause accidents, especially when driving at low speeds or in parking lots.
symptoms: Sudden
unintended acceleration
loss of control
and inability to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning voice guidance system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents.
symptoms: Inoperative voice guidance system
no audible voice or beeps
and inability to use navigation assistance.
